   "body" : "**Context**:\r\nIn 0.17.0 Bitcoin Core added `sethdseed` [RPC command](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/12560) which allows users to set their own seed for the [HD wallet](https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0032.mediawiki).\r\n\r\nHowever, because Core internally interprets the seed as a `CKey`, it can only hold 256 bits.\r\n\r\n[BIP39](https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0039.mediawiki) defines a mnemonic code for generating wallet seeds. It is currently supported by some of the most popular wallets on the market. BIP39 uses 512-bit seeds.\r\n\r\n**Problem**:\r\nCore does not currently support BIP39-style seeds.\r\n\r\n**Proposal**:\r\nAdd partial support for BIP39 to Core by letting `sethdseed` accept a seed whose length is up to 512 bits.\r\n\r\nThoughts? If people feel this is something useful to have, I can start working on an implementation.",
